{
  "stem": "15396.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In fact, none of us who worked in that organization had very good records at the State Department.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But Mrs.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Shipley happened to have been Polish and she was in charge of the Passport Division.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all these things came through her thing, and she knew about my friendship with the Poles and all.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I have a feeling that-- that she sort of softened down some of the-- where I was concerned.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the State Department wanted us to get out of France.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They did nothing to help us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In fact, put everything they could in our way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, was much-- I-- I drove an ambulance with the French army, an American volunteer ambulance corps, and when the-- France was overrun, we smuggled some British soldiers and all out of a hospital and took them-- when we ran out, or when were low on gas in-- in the-- in the ambulance, we put them on a freight train and we arrived in Marseilles.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's where I found a thing that was going to help us very much with the Jewish question later.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When you went out of the station, Gare Saint Charles, beautiful stairway there and all, you had to pass by the-- the control, and they asked for your papers, and your-- your ticket, which we didn't have, with being on a freight train.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We'd walk down the-- the tracks to get into the station, because the freight yards were some distance away.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we saw that they were investigating these papers, and we knew it, actually, but I don't know why we didn't know it before.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we went in, you  know, one of these bistros there, the-- beside the tracks to-- to get a little courage.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
